value.0: Svirfneblin are slightly smaller than their rock gnome cousins, but their thin, wiry, gnarled frames are just as strong. Svirfneblin have rock-coloured skin ranging in hue from medium brown to brownish grey, and their eyes are grey. Male svirfneblin are completely bald, while female deep gnomes have stringy grey hair.

A diabolical crossbow; with each pull of the trigger a flaming bolt springs forth, easily burning through the flesh of a foe. Used commonly by assassins, it enchances the wearers sight of hearing and vision, while being sturdy built enough to give it extreme precision and might.

Long ago, mind flayers conquered and captured a clan of dwarves known as the Duergar from the dwarven kingdom of Shanatar.  After decades of torture and enslavement (including experimentation) in the hands of the illithids, the gray dwarves (or duergar) gained their freedom from their masters after an uprising.  However, they emerged as a bitter, twisted race, though they retained many of the augmented powers they gained through the tests.
